bored-ape-yacht-club.websiteDescription:
## Bored Ape Yacht Club

The Bored Ape Yacht Club is a project by Yuga Labs that consists of 10,000 ape-themed NFTs with various qualities and distinctive attributes. BAYC, like most PFP-based NFTs, was influenced by CryptoPunks, the first of several NFT efforts aimed at creating a collection of figures with distinct qualities and rarity levels.

While this is a given, the Yuga Labs company has enhanced the overall theme of PFP-based NFTs. Now, the owners of Bored Apes are instantly members of an exclusive club with benefits starting from early access to new selections to getting the intellectual property rights for sales related to the acquired Bored Apes, such as when using the Apes likeness.

### Bored Ape Yacht Club: A Brief History

Just a year ago, the four thirty-somethings behind Bored Ape Yacht Club, a network of 10,000 NFTs (non-fungible tokens) that contain cartoonish primates and unlock virtual worlds, were living humble lives and doing day jobs while focusing on personal projects. 

They're now multimillionaires who made their fortune creating edgy artworks that also serve as membership cards and a platform for a loose crypto community of eccentrics. Is there anything more amazing than that?

The incredible nature of it all stems from the recent ubiquity of images of grungy apes with disdainful looks on their faces and human clothing on their colorful or metal bodies all over the web. 

The majority of the Apes appears to be figures from a hipster comic; some are vaping and wear 3D eye glasses, while others have bomber jackets, baseball caps, and grills. These digital images are quite popular on the internet, and you might see someone from your group with a BAYC Ape, like BAYC Apes in streetwear, as their profile picture.

### Bored Ape Yacht Club: Core Founders

The entire plot of BAYC focuses on the plot of these wealthy but bored people forming an exclusive club and hanging out at a social club/bar in the near future. The NFT collection's ape-themed characters illustrate the many personalities and behaviors you'd expect from a futurist crypto club.

Yuga Labs was founded by two friends, Gargamel and Gordon Goner, who use aliases. Curiously, Gordon Goner and Gargamel remained anonymous until recently, when researchers disclosed their names as Greg Solano and Wylie Aronow in a Buzzfeed piece published February 2022.

Since 2017, both have become "holders" and investors in the cryptocurrency industry. They ultimately realized that the advent of NFTs provided them with the opportunity to express their creative side while also actively contributing to the crypto revolution. They engaged two software developers (pseudonymous founders), Emperor Tomato Ketchup and No Sass, as part of the project's founders to help them achieve their aims.

These programmers handled the blockchain coding. These two were computer science experts, having studied the subject at the same institution as Solano did. They were, however, crypto-literate, having written their first lines of Solidity code, a smart contract programming language, in February 2021.

### BAYC: The Initial Response

One of the most well-known NFTs is Bored Apes, which the media have reported on. The Bored Ape Yacht Club surpassed CryptoPunks as the most expensive NFT in December 2021. 

For buyers who use their cartoon animals as avatars on social media, Bored Apes, like other character-based NFTs, would become a "status symbol." Many proprietors of Bored Ape NFTs acknowledged buying their Apes because of the marketing and advertising opportunities of having the copyrighted material of a Bored Ape NFT.

Yuga Labs employed illustrators, digital marketers, Discord community managers, and a CFO once Bored Ape NFTs became popular, and the chain of buyers grew exponentially. Aronow indicated that BAYC was seeking to be a "Web3 lifestyle firm" in reaction to the popularity of Bored Ape. ApeCoin DAO created its own coin, "ApeCoin" ($APE), on March 16, 2022, apart from Yuga Labs.

According to Markets Insider, the collection has garnered about 11,000 unique owners over time since its debut. As of this writing, an Ape has sold for an average of 84 Ether, or nearly $344,000. Companies have also been known to buy Bored Ape NFTs, with Adidas purchasing one in September 2021. In late 2021 and early 2022, many internet media outlets reported about celebrities acquiring Bored Apes.

### BAYC: The Future

The Bored Ape Yacht Club is slowly and steadily moving away from NFTs and toward being an "off-chain" brand that operates outside of the blockchain community. The Bored Apes are assimilating into the fashion world. 

Into The Metaverse, Adidas' first NFT initiative, was launched in partnership with many NFT businesses, including Bored Ape Yacht Club. Adidas, a famous clothing company, also purchased a Bored Ape Yacht Club NFT, which is now shown on the company's Twitter profile. Apes vs. Mutants, a mobile game, was released in January on both the App Store and Google Play Store.

However, what people are doing with their apes is amazing. The complete licensing rights that come with owning a Bored Ape NFT are being used in some innovative ways by holders. 

One Bored Ape owner gave his ape a Twitter account and gave him a narrative, transforming him into Jenkins, a valet at the Yacht Club. A real-world agency hired Jenkins in September. He'll have his biography, co-written by New York Times bestselling author Neil Strauss. You may believe NFTs is ridiculous and bad for the environment, but the Bored Apes aren't going anywhere soon

### The Bottom Line

Artists and programmers seldom remained around to create services around their collections or initiatives before the rise of the profile picture (PFP) non-fungible tokens. Therefore, they often profited from a single NFT fad before moving on to the next lucrative prospect. That is until Yuga Labs (a billion-dollar company) entered the market. That's the firm behind the Bored Ape Yacht Club (BAYC) collection, which is worth $3 billion.

Unlike most previous NFT projects, Yuga Labs implemented new and enhanced tactics for facilitating involvement and establishing a long-term NFT ecosystem. The company's decision to create a community-focused strategy for managing the BAYC brand contributed to its popularity. This is why many famous celebrity buyers, such as Gwyneth Paltrow, Lil Baby, Mark Cuban, Noam Galai, Post Malone, Neymar, and others interested in crypto assets, have each bought a Bored Ape for their collection.

bored-ape-kennel-club.websiteDescription:
## Bored Ape Kennel Club

The Bored Ape Kennel Club (BAKC) is a collection of non-fungible tokens (NFTs) on the Ethereum network. The 10,000 NFTs were dropped to all Bored Ape Yacht Club (BAYC) holders for free and currently 9,600 out of the 10,000 Bored Apes have claimed their canine buddy.

More recently, having a BAKC NFT in conjunction with a Bored Ape or Mutant Ape increased the number of $APE tokens airdropped to you in ApeCoin release, which had significant value for holders.

The issuance of this cryptocurrency delivered the first realized return on investment for Bored Ape holders, demonstrated that BAKC had ongoing use in the Bored Ape ecosystem, and further demonstrated that NFTs can be viable investments.

### Bored Ape Kennel Club NFT Collection: A Brief History 

#### The Initiative

The Bored Ape Kennel Club (BAKC) is a collection of 10,000 distinct NFT canines produced by Yuga Labs, creators of the Bored Ape Yacht Club (BAYC). The BAYC was a pioneering collection in the NFT space, and has grown into a vibrant community that has attracted celebrities, athletes, and companies to invest.

Yuga Labs decided to make the furry digital friends for all BAYC owners after the success of BAYC (similar to the related Mutant Ape Yacht Club (MAYC)). BAKC puppies, according to the project's developers, were intended to bring companionship to all Apes in the Bored Ape Yacht Club. Consequently, each member of the Bored Ape Yacht Club won an NFT dog.

Once minted, an owner could sell, hold, or transfer the BAKC Dog as they saw appropriate. The BAKC Dogs first appeared in the NFT world in June 2021. The companion NFT, Bored Ape Kennel Club, was an instant success due to the popularity of BAYC NFTs.

As noted by the BAYC designers, "It can feel lonely in the swamp at times. That is why every ape needs a four-legged friend."

As BAYC continues to deliver on its roadmaps, these cute pets may have some utility for holders in the future. 

As an added plus, Giving Block contributes royalties from the secondary sale of these dogs to animal shelters. The supplemental royalty charge of 2.5 percent was withdrawn after the first six weeks of their distribution.

### Bored Ape Kennel Club NFT Collection: The Key 
#### Considerations

Consider each token's characteristics before adding Bored Ape Kennel Club canines to your NFT collection.

#### The Categories

BAKC dogs can have traits in the following eight categories:

- Background
- Fur
- Back
- Eyes
- Head
- Neck
- Mouth
- Feet

#### The Key Traits

Each characteristic can be further classified.

1. #### Background

The following are examples of backgrounds:

- Bar
- Club exterior
- Outhouse
- Swamp

2. #### Furtypes
Fur types can include the following:

- Black
- Brown
- Cheetah
- Cyberpunk
- DMT
- Death Bot
- Galaxy
- Pink
- Radioactive
- Robot
- Tan

3. #### Black

The back can include the following:

- Basketball hoop
- Beer saddle
- Cyberpunk pack
- Doggie pack
- Mega rocket launcher
- Rocket launcher
- Service vest
- Toilet paper dispenser

4. #### Themes
Each dog also follows 1 of 9 different themes:

- Combat
- Robot
- Cyberpunk
- Zombie
- Trippy
- Golden
- Bayc
- Water
- Alcohol

Dogs from the Bored Ape Kennel Club might have several traits. The more uncommon the characteristics, the more valuable an NFT may become. An NFT marketplace allows investors to examine the features possessed by a BAKC dog and the rarity of each attribute.

### Bored Ape Kennel Club NFT Collection: The Floor Price Rate

The Bored Ape Kennel Club NFT collection has grown to include a new ATH floor price of 12 ETH. With a single NFT, the lowest price is now around $36,000.

Each of the Bored Ape Yacht Club's 10,000 NFTs was paired with one dog per BAYC, with the owner of the BAYC able to adopt (mint) the BAKC in June 2021. So BAYC owners could generate one Club Dog NFT at random by paying only gas fees for each BAYC they owned.

Surprisingly, 400 BAYC owners did not claim one for adoption, resulting in a total supply of 9.6k BAKC pups. Given the current value of gas, they may regret their decision to avoid the expenses. For the first six weeks, The proceeds went to the no-kill animal shelter organization Wright-Way Rescue.

The highest price paid for a BAKC this week (late April, early May 2022) was $104,000. It has solid gold fur, which just 1% of Bored Ape Kennel Club canines have. In addition, just 18% have closed eyes. In the randomized minting, some BAYC owners were fortunate enough to obtain club dogs with high rarity.

As ERC-721 tokens, each dog is unique and stored on the Ethereum blockchain. They have approximately 170 potential traits, some of which are more common than others. Yuga Labs made the Club Dog drop to provide entertainment and surprise while they focus on mutant-breeding and the treasure hunt.

There will be no more Club Dog drops. Therefore BAKC is a limited edition collection. Yuga Labs has continued its generous contributions by donating 10 million ApeCoin tokens to charity.      

### Bored Ape Kennel Club NFT Collection: The Roadmap

There is no clear plan for this non-fungible token collection. However, similar to past supply drops like BAYC, you may anticipate the devs adding unique value to these tokens that prior collection Ape owners may use in the future.

As with previous projects, owners may be able to obtain rare BAKC products and unlock limited edition items specific to the collection. Any single member may also get first dibs on the collections listed below.

### Bored Ape Kennel Club NFT Collection: The Future

The legendary Bored Apes will be accompanied on their voyage by this collection of 9,600 four-legged NFT companions. As a result, the project administrators may add significant functionality to Kennel NFTs this year, enhancing their value! 

### Bored Ape Kennel Club NFT Collection: The Clinch

Many reasons led to BAKC's success, but apart from time and the NFT market evolving in front of our eyes, the team created a fantastic tale through art and has continued to offer value to the project's holders. It will be amazing to see how much the Bored Ape brand spreads as owners use their commercial rights.

BAKC is a very speculative endeavor. In recent months, prices have climbed considerably, but they might decrease. The Apes' value stems from their scarcity and media attention. Investing your life wealth in an Ape is not a good idea; however, an ape may be rewarding if you have the money and are ready to take a risk. However, one thing is sure: BAKC is not going away anytime soon.

doodles.websiteDescription:
## The Doodles NFT collection

Doodles has grown into one of the most prominent and well-liked NFT projects in the world in just a few months. The bright line-drawn figures NFT assortment has practically overtaken the globe and is among the top PFP (profile-picture) NFT collections in both appeal and unit sales.

### Doodles NFT Collection: A Brief History

#### The Initiative

Evan Keast, Scott Martin, and Jordan Castro produced Doodles, a compilation of 10,000 generative NFTs. Tulip, Burnt Toast, and Poopie are the team's professional aliases, respectively, and are used as author names for the NFT collection.

Keast and Castro were already quite popular and well-versed in the NFT world before Doodles. In 2017, they also assisted in developing the iconic NFT project known as CryptoKitties. Martin has been minting his pieces for over a year and establishing his image inside the NFT realm.

The "Doodles NFT collection" incorporates original work by Martin, who generated hundreds of distinct visual characteristics for the series. However, in the end, the effort followed in the footsteps of precursors such as CryptoPunks, Bored Apes, and Cool Cats by arbitrarily combining and blending these unique features to produce the entire Doodles collections.

Humans, Kittens, Pickles, Apes, Intelligent Flames, Skeletons, Aliens, and more exist in the Doodles NFT environment. Doodles NFTs occur in varying degrees of uniqueness, characterized by their features, as is the case with virtually all generative avatar collections.

The Doodles team has never publicly published a list of the rarest and most common features. On the other hand, Skeletons, Kitties, Aliens, Apes, and Mascots have managed to resale for the largest prices.

#### The Unique Launch

The Doodles collection was launched by Keast, Castro, and Martin on October 17, 2021, with an initial price of 0.123 ETH per mint. The mint price was regarded to be somewhat outrageous at the time. Before Doodles, most PFP projects had mint prices of less than 0.1 ETH. The Doodles founders, on the other hand, chose this market value to secure an initial capital of 420 ETH.

During the project's launch, Doodles did something that appeared to have never been done before by a PFP initiative. The Doodles team shuttered the Doodles Discord server around a month before the initiative went online for minting when membership counts had reached a little over 1,000. This made it such that no newcomers could join, giving the project's membership an added layer of exclusivity.

This move was met with mixed reactions because it essentially granted whitelist access (priority minting) to a small number of people. Nevertheless, as the Doodles mint date approached, the project's popularity grew. Furthermore, the choice to shut down the Discord server was viewed as a novel approach to thank early NFT project supporters.

#### Market Growth

The Discord channel was relaunched soon after the complete supply of Doodles sold out, introducing a wave of new enthusiasts and aficionados into the group. In the weeks following this relaunch, a slew of NFT influencers and big-name celebrities joined Doodles as collectors, cementing the project's status as among the top trending PFP NFT groups on the planet.

While many avatar projects claim to be community-focused, Doodles appears to have been all about motivating its users from the beginning. Owning a Doodle and voting on group recommendations "makes the roadmap communal," according to the Doodles homepage. This aspect of the project has been increasingly evident in recent months due to its voting process and the pro-artist/anti-scam atmosphere.

#### The Voting Process and Unique Atmosphere

Doodles' whole ecology is essentially one DAO. Therefore, every Doodles owner has a say in how the DAO operates. Keast explained how the DoodleDAO treasury would function early on, claiming that 1 Doodle = 1 Vote in all of the DoodleBanks choices.

Doodles participants have had the opportunity to vote on suggestions for Doodles team scalability, Doodles live engagements, sponsoring a 3D Doodles initiative, and more thus far. The Doodles Forum and Doodles Discord provide an additional level of discussion for each suggestion.

Doodles immediately has become the basis for several copycat and knockoff products as among the most popular projects on the marketplace. Keast and the Doodles team seem to have foreseen this problem since they had already incorporated a derivative permission mechanism in their Discord.

Designers were encouraged to submit formal ideas for projects that were based on the primary Doodles set. Numerous Doodles community initiatives have been voted upon, with compilations such as Noodles and Pukenza resulting directly from the 1 Doodle = 1 Vote mechanism.

A scam warning line was also added to the Doodles server, encouraging people to "see something, say something." A large number of fake accounts and activities have been submitted there, and it appears that the channel has aided in the prevention of a lot of unauthorized Doodles knockoffs and possible frauds.

### Doodles NFT Collection Future: The Space Doodles

The Doodles floor price stayed between 1 and 5 ETH for months following its inception. Nevertheless, by the end of 2021, things had picked up steam. Keast and the rest of the Doodles group started releasing small cartoons around this time, hinting at something fresh on the way. 

This resulted in a surge in secondary sales, including some of the most significant sales ever.
When a project makes a significant revelation (e.g., Nike acquires RTFKT) or releases a collectors prize, there is usually a sudden increase in trading volume. Doodles NFT collection, though, has managed to keep the buzz going even a month after its announcement. So, what was the big news? Space Doodles.

Space Doodles is a new collection related to the main Doodles project. While Cool Pets, Bored Ape Kennel Club, KingFrogs, and others have helped collectors of their parent projects profit, Space Doodles appears to be a little different.

Rather than releasing a new collection of NFTs to complement their existing collection, the Doodles team plans to build a system that will allow Doodles owners to exchange their NFT for a new, spaceship-themed one.

### Doodles NFT Collection: The Crux

Given that Doodles was just founded a little over a year ago, the project's and its three founders' achievements are astounding. As of May 16th, the collection currently stands at roughly around 129,000 ETH volume traded.

While Doodles has a long way to go before they're considered a true candidate for the PFP NFT crown, the accumulation of colorful characters has unquestionably captured the hearts of endless NFT fans.

clone-x.websiteDescription:
## CLONE X NFT

Do you want to carry your NFT avatar around with you in the metaverse? If so, Clone X is the ideal NFT collection for you. Clone X's NFT collection is an NFT avatar set from RTFKT (pronounced "artifact") and Takashi Murakami, a famous Japanese artist. Clone X is one of the most successful NFT projects ever built.

Clone X's NFT collection is not only Metaverse-ready and offers high-end avatars, but it also heralds the start of a community-driven, high-quality environment. RTFKT Takashi Studios announced a public auction for its 20,000 Clone X 3D avatars NFTs on social media, an avatar collection for video games, movies, and other features within and outside the metaverse, in late November 2021.

Takashi Murakami has contributed to the collection by creating a slew of bright details in his trademark style. As a result, the Clone X avatars wear a wide range of apparel, accessories, and hairstyles. Each attribute is incredibly realistic because of RTFKT's integration with the Daz 3D platform.

### Clone X NFT Collection: A Brief History
#### The Narrative

The 3D avatar project describes its plot as being led by three extraterrestrials on the orbitar world near the Draco galaxy. According to the site, human qualities and behaviors are copied and implanted into metaverse clones to "evolve people into more sophisticated entities."

According to the founders of NFT Projects' public launch, the firm has based its brand on the metaverse, which "allows for a new method for fashion labels to develop not simply apparel but an entire living ecosystem.

People in the virtual world are not limited by the physical world, legacy, or other obstacles, as they are in the actual world. "Developing fashion pieces and character costumes to wear them and utilize them as your identity in the metaverse is a huge step forward for future fashion firms," Pagotto said.

Aside from NFTs, the metaverse was another massive topic in 2021, with everyone jumping on board. RTFKT, on the other hand, sees this as the beginning of a new age in which the value of physical belongings has transferred to digital assets to allow people to "live a more healthy and uncomplicated existence in the real world."

#### The Development

RTFKT NFTs secured $8 million in a preliminary fundraising round headed by Andreessen Horowitz in May 2021. RTFKT Studios claimed that it planned to utilize the funds to "push the NFT ecosystem forward and help define the future of virtual fashion and commerce in the metaverse" by creating an NFT marketplace, investing in projects, and expanding its workforce.

RTFKT created history by selling NFTs of digital shoes in partnership with artist Fewocious before the Clone X NFTs. In less than 7 minutes, the transactions for the shoes brought in more than $3 million.

RTFKT used graphics from previous NFT initiatives, such as the Bored Ape Yacht Club and CryptoPunks, for its digital shoes.

Following an announcement, secondary Clone X sales skyrocketed as investors flocked in, pushing the collection's floor price to 6 ETH, up from 3 ETH. That was before the biggest news broke.

As brands and businesses prepared for the metaverse, Nike hopped on board by purchasing RTFKT Studios, which "accelerates Nike's digital transformation and allows us to serve athletes and creators at the convergence of sport, creative, gaming, and culture," according to Nike President and CEO John Donahoe.

Internet behemoths such as Facebook have already poured billions of dollars into the metaverse. Apple CEO Tim Cook, who owns cryptocurrencies, has stated that the corporation sees "a lot of potentials" in the metaverse and is investing in it.

#### The Purchase

Clone X's popularity has caused its current floor price to rise to 14.4 ETH from the RTFKT pre-sale price of 0.05 ETH and 3 ETH for the Dutch auction.

You can acquire some of these colorful NFTs on the secondary market from crypto art buyers now that the enthusiasm around them has been on the rise and shows no signs of slowing down.

### Clone X Paid Homage to the Bored Ape Yacht Club

Bored Ape Yacht Club is a project by Yuga Labs that consists of 10,000 ape-themed NFTs with various qualities and distinctive attributes.

BAYC, like most PFP-based NFTs, has vast influence by CryptoPunks, the first of several NFT efforts aimed at creating characters with distinct qualities and rarity levels. Yuga Labs has elevated the entire concept of PFP-based NFTs.

Owners of Bored Apes are automatically members of an exclusive club with perks ranging from early access to new offerings to the possibility of receiving the commercial usage right to the purchased Bored Apes.

Clone X has paid homage to BAYC in various ways.

### Clone X NFT Collection: The Growth

The announcement that Clone X parent firm RTFKT was purchased by Nike resulted in a spike in sales volume and valuation for the NFT project. It occurred around the same time as other big news stories, including competitor Adidas entry into Web3.

Adidas' Into the Metaverse NFT collection featured a pre-mint period reserved for Bored Ape Yacht Club, Gmoney, and Pixel Vault NFT holders. Although several delays and issues during the process, the NFT collection eventually sold out at 0.2 Ethereum ETH/USD apiece.

The Sandbox, Bored Ape Yacht Club, and Mutant Ape Yacht Club remained in the top 10, with minor volume increases from the previous week.

### Clone X NFT Collection: Trouble

Since RTFKT revealed a metaverse-first avatar collection on November 27th, the pre-sale event for allowed collectors began, and Clone X Mintvile NFTs flooded the secondary market. The pre-sale NFTs' floor price was also higher, at 3.7 ETH. Unfortunately, as the November 29th public sale approached, issues piled up for the RTFKT team. 

The team had to suspend the Dutch auction public sale several hours after it started because the website and smart contracts were both under assault. Collectors, on the other hand, were dissatisfied with the choice. 

In a Dutch auction to distribute NFTs, the initial starting price is high, then progressively decreases. Collectors can purchase at any time, at the current price. Of course, you may wait for the price to drop, but NFTs tend to sell out rapidly.

Dutch auctions have recently gained popularity, though some NFT degens have frowned upon them. Pausing a Dutch auction if the price gets too low is an especially criticized practice. The RTFKT team delayed the Dutch auction midway for the Clone X mint, which some collectors perceived as an effort to maintain the price of NFTs relatively high.

### Clone X NFT Collection: The Future

Clone X represents the beginning of a new era for RTFKT and one of the first genesis avatars created in the NFT reality. When it comes to the metaverse and its impact on the future, a Clone X avatar will likely be in demand. The metaverse as a whole allows us to live a digital existence alongside the physical world.

### Clone X NFT Collection: The Final Words

In the NFT arena, PFP NFTs (ones where an individual will use the NFT as a digital profile picture) are the trendiest.  RTFKT's Clone X collection is now trending, attracting attention, transactions, and cash. Its ability to run on numerous platforms and be metaverse-ready speaks much about its potential.

NFT may see a lot of attraction in offering privileged access to its Clone X owners and linking it to the real world with actual objects. It also provides other benefits through upgrades and the long-term ecology that RTFKT creates around them. "Having a Clone will be a flex," Pagotto, the company's co-founder, said.

moonbirds.websiteDescription:
## Moonbirds NFT Collection

Moonbirds are much more than avatars. They're a group of 10,000 utility-enabled PFPs with a wide range of rarity-powered features. Furthermore, the longer you have a Moonbird, the more you can access a particular club and other privileges. We call it nesting.

This NFT is the PROOF Collective's second project to take the globe by storm. The alpha/social club had only been available to 1,000 people before Moonbirds. A wager on Moonbirds includes a chance on the PROOF team and the DAO they have assembled. Kevin Rose is the most well-known member of that team and the best bet.
Kevin Rose is the creator of Digg, as well as an entrepreneur and venture capitalist.

mutant-ape-yacht-club.openseaDescription: The MUTANT APE YACHT CLUB is a collection of up to 20,000 Mutant Apes that can only be created by exposing an existing Bored Ape to a vial of MUTANT SERUM or by minting a Mutant Ape in the public sale.
mutant-ape-yacht-club.websiteDescription:
## Mutant Ape Yacht Club NFT

The Mutant Ape Yacht Club can be seen not as a derivative project but as a companion project of the Bored Ape Yacht Club. The general idea of the Mutant Ape Yacht Club is that the Mutant Apes are formed when mutant serums are administered to the NFTs in the collection of Bored Ape Yacht Club.

Rather than derivative pieces, these new mutations within this blockchain project number 20,000  digital collectibles of Mutant Apes created with a special serum. It is one of the cool projects to follow up from its earlier version: the Bored Ape Yacht Club.

This non-fungible tokens collection has risen to prominence like its parent organization and stands on the list of billion-dollar companies or collections in the NFT world. Developed by Yuga Labs, this better than derivative collection of Mutant Apes has incorporated celebrities, such as star basketball player Stephen Curry and members of English French-based band Stereolab.

The club for Apes has garnered immense support and investment within a year after its launch. At current times, the parent community, the Bored Ape Yacht Club, stands near the top of the secondary market of NFT sales with a market volume of 551,000 ETH.

On the contrary, the Mutant Ape Yacht Club is leading in the second position with a market volume of 382,000 ETH. Hence, these collections, related to the Kennel Club BAYC collection, are the undisputed champions of the OpenSea crypto community by bagging the two of the top three positions.

### A Glance at The History of Mutant Ape Yacht Club

#### Creators of the Appealing Collection of Mutant Apes

This (some would say) derivative project is one of the most creative projects in the metaverse universe with art pieces of 20,000 Mutant Apes. Yuga Labs is the sole owner and creator of this club for Apes. There has been significant development ever since the inception of this collection.

Different categories of serums are available for the Ape holders to convert their Bored Ape Yacht Club collectibles into a Mutant version, along with keeping the previous BAYC NFT intact. The creators are working continuously for the development of this NFT community and have created enough value to keep it in the two of the top three slots on OpenSea.

#### Breaking Down the Storyline

The story begins on 29 April 2021 with the first public sale of the Bored Ape Yacht Club. The storyline portrays a metaverse decentralized community with Apes as the leading figures. The Apes have taken over, and that is the new world order in this part of the metaverse.

The three categories of serums are M1, M2, and M3 (Mega Mutant). The M1 and M2, when used with a Bored Ape, will create a Mutant figure resembling the parent version. However, the M3 serum has different rarities and will create a diverse and completely new digital art of Mutants.

The Apes are ruling and propagating through activities, including community-building. The roadmap is extended with this Mutant Ape Yacht Club, which adds to the BAYC NFT collections. A serum is created and is available to token holders of the Bored Ape Yacht Club art community.

The Bored Ape Yacht club sells serum of different potency. After being injected with serums, a new version of apes, Mutant Apes, come into existence. Exclusive communities have been created within the Mutant version of this NFT project to keep on increasing the growth rate.

### The Market Impact of Mutant Ape Yacht Club

According to the blockchain analytics, the Mutant Ape Yacht Club is a growing collection (not a growing *company*) and is third on the list of OpenSea NFTs in terms of all-time market volume. The public sale of these non-fungible tokens, aided by smart contracts, started at low prices.

However, while there was an intriguing price discovery when the collection first minted, the NFTs have seen a sharp increase after they gained immense popularity in the NFT world. The digital collectibles of the Mutant Ape Yacht Club were sold based on a Dutch auction mechanism.

The Dutch auction mechanism is a bidding series for an available commodity. In this methodology, bids are placed on the respective objects, and the highest bid is awarded the sale. If there are no bids, the price decreases after a certain time frame. That method has been prevalent in the trading of NFTs on the OpenSea platform ever since its inception. This Dutch auction pricing mechanism is one of the most common tools or factors amongst projects selling NFTs.

During the time of launch, each digital collection of Mutant Apes was priced at 3 ETH, and now the floor price has reached a whopping cost of 40 ETH, one of the highest in the NFT community. The traded volume of Mutant Ape Yacht Club is only third to its parent collection and the CryptoPunks collection.

Currently, the ERC-20 tokens of these Ape communities are the most fast-paced NFTs. They have been at the top of leaderboards for quite some time, and these general blockchain applications are not going to vacate the positions easily. They will keep on ruling the market unless a tough competitor intrudes in to challenge the rule of Mutant Apes.

### Blockchain Game: A Future Leap of the Bored Ape Yacht Club

The creators of these two collections vowed to take the initiative in a future blockchain game. The game was called Mutant Ape Arcade Game. However, it is only available for a limited period of three days.

The sole aim of playing this game revolved around the idea of defeating Mutant Apes and escaping the Mutant World. The winning member was entitled to different perks within the community. The provision of a gaming component with community membership is a great addition and a lucrative opportunity for members.

### Discord Community of Mutant Ape Yacht Club

The Discord community managers of this club are leading the overall development of the community. However, the developers have provided equal opportunities to all the members of the Discord by having considered their viewpoints.

It is a club for people and is not controlled by any individual entity. Furthermore, the purpose of the community is to bond stronger and make the Mutant Apes a reckoning force in the metaverse. Furthermore, the holders of NFTs will be provided exclusive membership benefits and will be engaged in community activities.

### Mutant Ape Yacht Club: Final Thoughts

Mutant Ape Yacht Club is the leading collection in the OpenSea NFT world. It stands third to its parent collection and CryptoPunks (both owned by company Yuga Labs) and has a whopping collectibles of 20,000 characters of Mutant Apes. The developers have ensured the provision of serums to the members of Bored Ape Yacht Club, which they can use to get a Mutant version.

The popularity of this NFT project has soared beyond imagination, and it has taken second place in the NFT rankings in a short period. Keeping in check the market analytics is perfect for predicting that the value of this digital asset will keep on increasing in the days to come.
